# What is the long-term impact that the shelling in Nikopol will have on the region's civilians?

## Summary
The shelling of Nikopol in the Zaporizhzhia region of Ukraine, combined with shelling in the neighboring Kharkiv region and the Donetsk region, has caused immense human suffering and destruction of residential buildings, power lines, and water supply systems <font color=#FF3399>[1, 2, 3, 4, 5]</font>. As a result, thousands of families are now without water and energy, with homes and gas pipelines damaged <font color=#FF3399>[3, 4]</font>. This shelling has been ongoing since February, when Russian President Vladimir Putin invaded Ukraine <font color=#FF3399>[2]</font>, and has caused severe long-term impacts on the regionâ€™s civilians.

